{"lemma":"دَرَجِ","slug":"دَرَجِ","root":"د.ر.ج","root_slug":"د-ر-ج","root_link":"/words/roots/د-ر-ج","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":6,"pos_tags":["noun","verb"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":28},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n12379","","n12384","n12385","n12386","n12392"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%AF%D9%8E%D8%B1%D9%8E%D8%AC%D9%90"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to step, step onward, walk"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to proceed or ascend gradually"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to graduate"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to be or become customary"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to be a custom, be the fashion"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to be current, have currency"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to be used to, to be accustomed, to have the habit"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to pass, depart, disappear, get destroyed"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to die","tags":["euphemistic"]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to roll up or close a book"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to gradate, to divide up"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to circulate, to float"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to fold up, to curl up"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"verbal noun of دَرَجَ (daraja, “to roll up”) (form I)","tags":["form-of","noun-from-verb"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"roll of paper"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"volume"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"fold"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"entering into a book or register"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"putting in"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"road, path"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"staircase, ladder"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"mediator"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"copybook"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"drawer"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"plural of دُرَجَة (duraja)","tags":["form-of","plural"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"plural of دَرَجَة (daraja)","tags":["form-of","plural"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"plural of دُرْجَة (durja)","tags":["form-of","plural"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"plural of دُرَجَّة (durajja)","tags":["form-of","plural"]}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Compare Ge'ez ድርገት (dərgät), Hebrew דֶּרֶג (déreḡ), Classical Syriac ܕܪܓܐ, Aramaic דרגא."},"ipa":null,"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n12379","headword_ar":"دَرَجَ","root":"drj","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", (S, Msb, K,) aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, Msb,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"duruwjN","text_ar":"دُرُوجٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Msb, K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"darajaAnN","text_ar":"دَرَجَانٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,) said of a man, and of a [lizard of the kind called]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Dab~","text_ar":"ضَبّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He went on foot;"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"went step by step; stepped along;"},{"kind":"text","text":"] or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"walked:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K:) and said of a child,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he walked a little, at his first beginning to walk:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb, TA: *) or, said of an old man, and of a child, and of a bird of the kind called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qaTFA","text_ar":"قَطًا"},{"kind":"text","text":", aor. as above, inf. n. ["},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"duruwjN","text_ar":"دُرُوجٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"darojN","text_ar":"دَرْجٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"darajaAnN","text_ar":"دَرَجَانٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"dariyjN","text_ar":"دَرِيجٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he walked with a weak gait; crept along;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"went,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"walked, leisurely, slowly, softly,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"gently."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b2-  [Hence,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"daraja qaronN baEoda","text_ar":"دَرَجَ قَرْنٌ بَعْدَ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qaronK","text_ar":"قَرْنٍ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Generation after generation passed away."},{"kind":"text","text":"(A.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"daraja Alqawomu","text_ar":"دَرَجَ القَوْمُ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The people passed away,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"perished, none of them remaining;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, A, K;) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AndrjwA","text_ar":"اندرجوا","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":". (S, K.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"daraja","text_ar":"دَرَجَ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He left no progeny,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"offspring:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(As, S, K:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he died, and left no progeny,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"offspring:"},{"kind":"text","text":"[opposed to"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aEoqaba","text_ar":"اَعْقَبَ"},{"kind":"text","text":":] but you do not say so of every one who has died: (TA:) or it signifies also [simply]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he died:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Aboo-Tálib, S, A, Msb:) so in the prov.,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^ako*abu","text_ar":"اَكْذَبُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mano dab~a wadaraja","text_ar":"مَنْ دَبَّ وَدَرَجَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Msb)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The most lying of the living and the dead."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S.) Or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"daraja","text_ar":"دَرَجَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies, (K,) or signifies also, (S,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He went his way;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K;) and so"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"darija","text_ar":"دَرِجَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", [aor."},{"kind":"text","text":",] like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"samiEa","text_ar":"سَمِعَ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (K.)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"layosa h`*aA","text_ar":"لَيْسَ هٰذَا"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"biEu$~iki faA@dorujiY","text_ar":"بِعُشِّكِ فَا@دْرُجِى"},{"kind":"text","text":", i. e. ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"This is not thy nest, therefore"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"go thou away,"},{"kind":"text","text":"is a saying occurring in a"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xuTobap","text_ar":"خُطْبَة"},{"kind":"text","text":"of El-Hajjáj, addressed to him who applies himself to a thing not of his business to do; or to him who is at ease in an improper time; wherefore he is thus ordered to be diligent and in motion. (TA. [See also art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"E$","text_ar":"عش"},{"kind":"text","text":".]) ―         -b3-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"darajato","text_ar":"دَرَجَتْ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^adorajato","text_ar":"اَدْرَجَتْ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"She"},{"kind":"text","text":"(a camel)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"went beyond the year"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"from the day when she was covered"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"without bringing forth."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K.) ―         -b4-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"darajati Alr~iyHu","text_ar":"دَرَجَتِ الرِّيحُ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The wind left marks,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"lines,"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"ripples,"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"upon the sand."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b5-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"darajati Alr~iyHu biAlHaSaA","text_ar":"دَرَجَتِ الرِّيحُ بِالحَصَا"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The wind passed violently over the pebbles"},{"kind":"text","text":"[app."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"so as to make them move along:"},{"kind":"text","text":"see also 10]. (K.)       -A2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"darija","text_ar":"دَرِجَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He rose in grade, degree, rank, condition,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"station."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA.) ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He kept to the plain and manifest way"},{"kind":"text","text":"in religion or in speech. (K, TA.)       -A3-  Also (i. e."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"darija","text_ar":"دَرِجَ"},{"kind":"text","text":")"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He continued to eat the kind of bird called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"dur~aAj","text_ar":"دُرَّاج"},{"kind":"text","text":". (K.)       -A4-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"daraja","text_ar":"دَرَجَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"as a trans. v.: see 4, in two places."}],"source_refs":["S","Msb","K","As","TA"]},{"entry_id":"n12384","headword_ar":"دَرْجٌ","root":"drj","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"darajN","text_ar":"دَرَجٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in two places.       -A2-  Also, and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"darajN","text_ar":"دَرَجٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A thing in,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"upon, which one writes;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K;) ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a scroll,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"long paper,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the like, generally composed of several pieces joined together, which is folded"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"rolled up:"},{"kind":"text","text":"] and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mudorajN","text_ar":"مُدْرَجٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", [used as a subst.,]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a writing folded"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"rolled up;"},{"kind":"text","text":"pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"madaAriju","text_ar":"مَدَارِجُ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (Har p. 254:) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mdrjp","text_ar":"مدرجة"},{"kind":"text","text":"[app. ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mudorajapN","text_ar":"مُدْرَجَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^adoraja","text_ar":"اَدْرَجَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"“ he folded ” or “ rolled up, ” with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"p","text_ar":"ة"},{"kind":"text","text":"added to transfer it from the predicament of part. ns. to that of substs.,] signifies [in like manner]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a paper upon which one writes a"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"risaAlap","text_ar":"رِسَالَة"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"message,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.],"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and which one folds,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"rolls up;"},{"kind":"text","text":"pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"madaAriju","text_ar":"مَدَارِجُ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (Har p. 246.) ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fiY daroji AlkitaAbi","text_ar":"فِى دَرْجِ الكِتَابِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fiY Tay~ihi","text_ar":"فِى طَيِّهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[lit."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Within the folding of the writing;"},{"kind":"text","text":"meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"infolded,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"included, in the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"writing"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; (S, A, TA;) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fiY vinoyihi","text_ar":"فِى ثِنْيِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[which means the same]; (A;) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fiY daAxilihi","text_ar":"فِى دَاخِلِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[an explicative adjunct, meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in the inside of the writing"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (TA.) You say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^anofa*otuhu fiY daroji AlkitaAbi","text_ar":"اَنْفَذْتُهُ فِى دَرْجِ الكِتَابِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I transmitted it in the inside of the writing"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (S, TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jaEalahu fiY daroji AlkitaAbi","text_ar":"جَعَلَهُ فِى دَرْجِ الكِتَابِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He put it in the inside of the writing"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (A, L, TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fiY daroji AlkitaAbi ka*aA wa ka*aA","text_ar":"فِى دَرْجِ الكِتَابِ كَذَا وَ كَذَا"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"In the inside of the writing are such and such things;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in the writing are"},{"kind":"text","text":"enclosed, or included, or written, or mentioned,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"such and such things;"},{"kind":"text","text":"this being commonly meant by the phrase"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fiY TaY~i AlkitaAbi","text_ar":"فِى طَىِّ الكِتَابِ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"k*A wk*A","text_ar":"كذا وكذا"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (TA.)"}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n12385","headword_ar":"دُرْجٌ","root":"drj","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A woman's"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hif$","text_ar":"حِفش"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (S, K;) i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a small receptacle of the kind called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"safaT","text_ar":"سَفَط"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in which a woman keeps her perfumes and apparatus,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"implements:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) [accord. to the K, it is a coll. gen. n.; for it is there added, (I think in consequence of a false reading in a trad.,)] the n. un. is with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"p","text_ar":"ة"},{"kind":"text","text":": and the pl. [of mult.] is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"dirajapN","text_ar":"دِرَجَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and [of pauc.]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^adoraAjN","text_ar":"اَدْرَاجٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (K.)"}],"source_refs":["TA"]},{"entry_id":"n12386","headword_ar":"دَرَجٌ","root":"drj","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A way, road,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"path;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, L, K;) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"darojN","text_ar":"دَرْجٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (L:) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"madorajapN","text_ar":"مَدْرَجَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, A) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"madorajN","text_ar":"مَدْرَجٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A, K) signify ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the same;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a way by,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"through, which one goes"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"passes; a way which one pursues; a course,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"route;"},{"kind":"text","text":"syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ma*ohabN","text_ar":"مَذْهَبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"masolakN","text_ar":"مَسْلَكٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mamar~N","text_ar":"مَمَرٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (A;) and particularly the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"way along which a boy and the wind &c. go;"},{"kind":"text","text":"as also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"darajN","text_ar":"دَرَجٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; respecting which last, in relation to the wind, see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"daruwjN","text_ar":"دَرُوجٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (L:) or ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"madorajN","text_ar":"مَدْرَجٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a road;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a cross-road;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a bending road;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and its pl. is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"madaArijN","text_ar":"مَدَارِجٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (Msb:) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"madorajapN","text_ar":"مَدْرَجَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"is explained by Er-Rághib as signifying"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a beaten way"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"road:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and it signifies also the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"course by which things pass, on a road &c.:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"main part"},{"kind":"text","text":"of a road: and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a rugged"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"road such as is termed"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"vaniy~ap","text_ar":"ثَنِيَّة"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"between mountains:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) the pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"darajN","text_ar":"دَرَجٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, L) and of ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"darojN","text_ar":"دَرْجٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(L) is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^adoraAjN","text_ar":"اَدْرَاجٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, L) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"diraAjN","text_ar":"دِرَاجٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", which occurs in a prov. cited below: (Meyd:) and the pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"madorajapN","text_ar":"مَدْرَجَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"madaArijN","text_ar":"مَدَارِجٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S, TA:)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^akamapK","text_ar":"اَكَمَةٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"madaAriju","text_ar":"مَدَارِجُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the roads that lie across a hill such as is termed"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Akmp","text_ar":"اكمة"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.) You say"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^adoraAjaka","text_ar":"اَدْرَاجَكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Go thy way, as thou camest."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA from a trad.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rajaEa darajahu","text_ar":"رَجَعَ دَرَجَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rajaEa A^adoraAjahu","text_ar":"رَجَعَ اَدْرَاجَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Sb, S, K) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_idoraAjahu","text_ar":"اـِدْرَاجَهُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EalaY A_idoraAjihi","text_ar":"عَلَى اـِدْرَاجِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(IAar)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He returned by the way by which he had come."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K, TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rajaEa darajahu","text_ar":"رَجَعَ دَرَجَهُ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He returned to the thing,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"affair, that he had left."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rajaEa EalaY A^adoraAjihi","text_ar":"رَجَعَ عَلَى اَدْرَاجِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rajaEa darajahu AlA^aw~ala","text_ar":"رَجَعَ دَرَجَهُ الاَوَّلَ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He returned without having been able to accomplish what he desired."},{"kind":"text","text":"(IAar.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Aisotamar~a darajahu","text_ar":"اِسْتَمَرَّ دَرَجَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^adoraAjahu","text_ar":"اَدْرَاجَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He kept on his way; persevered in his course"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"huwa EalaY daraji ka*aA","text_ar":"هُوَ عَلَى دَرَجِ كَذَا"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He is on the way of,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"to, such a thing."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) And ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ait~axa*uwA daArahu madorajapF","text_ar":"اِتَّخَذُوا دَارَهُ مَدْرَجَةً","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"madorajFA","text_ar":"مَدْرَجًا","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"They made his house a way through which to pass."},{"kind":"text","text":"(A.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"lih`*aA","text_ar":"لِهٰذَا"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"h`*aA AlA^amoru madorajapN","text_ar":"هٰذَا الاَمْرُ مَدْرَجَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"This thing,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"affair, is a way that leads to"},{"kind":"page_break","n":869},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"this."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlHaq~i","text_ar":"الحَقِّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Aimo$a fiY madaAriji","text_ar":"اِمْشَ فِى مَدَارِجِ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Walk thou in the ways of truth."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*ahaba","text_ar":"ذَهَبَ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"damuhu A^adoraAja Alr~iyaAHi","text_ar":"دَمُهُ اَدْرَاجَ الرِّيَاحِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"His blood went for nothing;"},{"kind":"text","text":"[lit.,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in the ways of the winds;"},{"kind":"text","text":"meaning]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"so that no account was taken of it, and it was not avenged."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, A, * K.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xal~ daraja AlD~ab~i","text_ar":"خَلّ دَرَجَ الضَّبِّ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Leave thou the way of the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Db~","text_ar":"ضبّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[a species of lizard], (S, Meyd,) and oppose not thyself to him, (TA,) lest he pass between thy feet, and thou become angry ("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fatanotafixa","text_ar":"فَتَنْتَفِخَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"): (S, Meyd:) a prov., applied in the case of demanding security from evil. (Meyd. [See another reading, and explanations thereof, in Har p. 220, or in Freytag's Arab. Prov. i. 437.]) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mano yarud~u AlfuraAta Eano diraAjihi","text_ar":"مَنْ يَرُدُّ الفُرَاتَ عَنْ دِرَاجِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^adoraAjihi","text_ar":"اَدْرَاجِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", accord. to different readings, with two different pls. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"darajN","text_ar":"دَرَجٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Who will turn back Euphrates from its course?"},{"kind":"text","text":"a prov. applied to an impossible affair. (Meyd.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mano yarud~u Als~ayola","text_ar":"مَنْ يَرُدُّ السَّيْلَ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EalaY A^adoraAjihi","text_ar":"عَلَى اَدْرَاجِهِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Who will turn back the torrent to its channels?"},{"kind":"text","text":"another prov. so applied. (Meyd.)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"daraju sayolK","text_ar":"دَرَجُ سَيْلٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sayolK","text_ar":"سَيْلٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"madoraju","text_ar":"مَدْرَجُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"signify"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The way by which a torrent descends in the bendings of valleys."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b2-  [Hence, perhaps, as denoting a way, or means,] (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A mediator between two persons for the purpose of effecting a reconciliation."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K.) ―         -b3-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^anaAa daraju yadayoka","text_ar":"اَنَاَ دَرَجُ يَدَيْكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"means (tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I am submissive,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"obedient, to thee;"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I will not disobey thee:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A, TA: *) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"drj","text_ar":"درج"},{"kind":"text","text":"used in this sense does not assume a dual nor a pl. form: [therefore] you say also,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"humo daraju yadika","text_ar":"هُمْ دَرَجُ يَدِكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"They are submissive,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"obedient, to thee."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b4-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"daraju Alr~amoli","text_ar":"دَرَجُ الرَّمْلِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlmaA='i","text_ar":"المَا=ءِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signify ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The ripples of sand"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of water;"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"what are seen upon sand,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"upon water, when moved by the wind."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Az and TA in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hbk","text_ar":"حبك"},{"kind":"text","text":".) See"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"daruwjN","text_ar":"دَرُوجٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". ―         -b5-  See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"darajapN","text_ar":"دَرَجَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in two places.       -A2-  And see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"darojN","text_ar":"دَرْجٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"."}],"source_refs":["L","S","A","K","Msb","TA","Meyd","Sb","IAar"]},{"entry_id":"n12392","headword_ar":"دُرَّجٌ","root":"drj","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Great and difficult affairs"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"circumstances."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K.) You say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"waqaEa fulaAnN fiY dur~ajK","text_ar":"وَقَعَ فُلَانٌ فِى دُرَّجٍ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Such a one fell into great and difficult affairs"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"circumstances."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.)"}],"source_refs":[]}]},"classical_definitions":null}